<p>wall of the trench and presently felt a big piece of wood hit me on the body.&nbsp;When the bombardment was over I cleared the mud away from my gear and lay down to sleep.&nbsp;Early the following night shrapnel began to come my way pretty thick, so I moved to another spot further up the trench.&nbsp;While I was at work next day a bomber sitting on my pack received nine wounds and my greatcoat was simply riddled with pieces of shell and wire.</p>
